---
layout: layouts/tool.njk
title: JSON Formatter & Validator
description: Free online JSON formatter, validator, and beautifier. Format, minify, and validate JSON with syntax highlighting and error detection. No signup required.
keywords: JSON formatter, JSON beautifier, JSON validator, JSON minifier, format JSON online, validate JSON, pretty print JSON
permalink: /tools/json-formatter/
toolId: json-formatter
toolJs: json-formatter.js
ogImage: json-formatter.jpg
---
{% set toolData = tools | selectattr("id", "equalto", toolId) | first %}

{% block schema %}
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  "itemListElement": [
    {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "{{ site.url }}/"},
    {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Tools", "item": "{{ site.url }}/#tools"},
    {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "{{ toolData.name }}", "item": "{{ site.url }}{{ page.url }}"}
  ]
}
</script>
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebApplication",
  "name": "{{ toolData.fullName }}",
  "description": "{{ description }}",
  "url": "{{ site.url }}{{ page.url }}",
  "applicationCategory": "DeveloperApplication",
  "operatingSystem": "Any",
  "browserRequirements": "Requires JavaScript",
  "offers": {"@type": "Offer", "price": "0", "priceCurrency": "USD"},
  "featureList": ["Format/beautify JSON", "Minify JSON", "Validate JSON with error highlighting", "Syntax highlighting", "Customizable indentation"],
  "author": {"@type": "Organization", "name": "{{ site.name }}", "url": "{{ site.url }}"}
}
</script>
{% endblock %}

{% block head %}
<style>
  .json-key { color: #881391; }
  .json-string { color: #1a1aa6; }
  .json-number { color: #1c00cf; }
  .json-boolean { color: #0d22aa; }
  .json-null { color: #808080; }
  [data-theme="dark"] .json-key { color: #9cdcfe; }
  [data-theme="dark"] .json-string { color: #ce9178; }
  [data-theme="dark"] .json-number { color: #b5cea8; }
  [data-theme="dark"] .json-boolean { color: #569cd6; }
  [data-theme="dark"] .json-null { color: #808080; }
  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    :root:not([data-theme="light"]) .json-key { color: #9cdcfe; }
    :root:not([data-theme="light"]) .json-string { color: #ce9178; }
    :root:not([data-theme="light"]) .json-number { color: #b5cea8; }
    :root:not([data-theme="light"]) .json-boolean { color: #569cd6; }
    :root:not([data-theme="light"]) .json-null { color: #808080; }
  }
  #json-highlighted { white-space: pre-wrap; word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 'Monaco', 'Menlo', 'Ubuntu Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.5; }
  #json-error { background-color: #fef2f2; border: 1px solid #fecaca; color: #b91c1c; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; border-radius: 0.375rem; margin-top: 0.5rem; font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.875rem; }
  [data-theme="dark"] #json-error { background-color: #450a0a; border-color: #7f1d1d; color: #fca5a5; }
  .json-stats { display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; flex-wrap: wrap; font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--text-muted); }
  .json-stats dt { font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-secondary); }
  .json-stats dd { margin: 0; font-family: monospace; }
  .json-stat-item { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.25rem; }
</style>
{% endblock %}

<div class="tool-container">
  <div class="tool-input-group">
    <div class="input-header">
      <label for="json-input" class="input-label">Enter JSON</label>
      <button type="button" id="sample-json" class="btn btn-text btn-sm">Load Sample</button>
    </div>
    <textarea id="json-input" class="tool-textarea" rows="10" placeholder='{"key": "value", "array": [1, 2, 3]}' spellcheck="false"></textarea>
  </div>

  <div class="tool-options">
    <div class="option-group">
      <label for="json-indent" class="option-label">Indentation</label>
      <select id="json-indent" class="tool-select">
        <option value="2" selected>2 Spaces</option>
        <option value="4">4 Spaces</option>
        <option value="tab">Tab</option>
      </select>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="tool-actions">
    <button type="button" id="format-json" class="btn btn-primary">Format</button>
    <button type="button" id="minify-json" class="btn btn-secondary">Minify</button>
    <button type="button" id="validate-json" class="btn btn-secondary">Validate</button>
    <button type="button" id="copy-json" class="btn btn-secondary">Copy</button>
    <button type="button" id="clear-json" class="btn btn-ghost">Clear</button>
  </div>

  <div id="json-error" class="hidden" role="alert"></div>

  <div class="tool-output-group">
    <div class="output-header">
      <span class="output-label">Output</span>
      <div class="json-stats">
        <div class="json-stat-item"><dt>Size</dt><dd id="json-size">-</dd></div>
        <div class="json-stat-item"><dt>Keys</dt><dd id="json-keys">-</dd></div>
        <div class="json-stat-item"><dt>Depth</dt><dd id="json-depth">-</dd></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tool-output-wrapper">
      <pre id="json-output" class="tool-output tool-output-placeholder">Formatted JSON will appear here</pre>
      <pre id="json-highlighted" class="tool-output hidden"></pre>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<section class="content-section">
  <h2>How to Use</h2>
  <div class="steps">
    <div class="step"><div class="step-number">1</div><div class="step-content"><h3>Paste Your JSON</h3><p>Enter or paste your JSON data into the input field. You can also click "Load Sample" to see an example.</p></div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="step-number">2</div><div class="step-content"><h3>Choose an Action</h3><p><strong>Format</strong> to beautify with proper indentation, <strong>Minify</strong> to compress, or <strong>Validate</strong> to check for errors.</p></div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="step-number">3</div><div class="step-content"><h3>Copy the Result</h3><p>Click "Copy" to copy the formatted or minified JSON to your clipboard.</p></div></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="content-section">
  <h2>FAQ</h2>
  <div class="faq-list">
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-question">What is JSON formatting?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer"><p>JSON formatting (also called beautifying) adds proper indentation and line breaks to make JSON human-readable.</p></div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-question">What's the difference between formatting and minifying?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer"><p>Formatting adds whitespace for readability. Minifying removes all unnecessary whitespace to reduce file size.</p></div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-question">Is my data secure?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. All processing happens in your browser. Your data never leaves your device.</p></div>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="content-section">
  <h2>Related Tools</h2>
  <div class="related-tools">
    {% for tool in tools %}
    {% if tool.id != toolId %}
    <a href="/tools/{{ tool.id }}/" class="related-tool-link">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" width="16" height="16">{{ tool.icon | safe }}</svg>
      {{ tool.name }}
    </a>
    {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
